        <h2>Business Analysis and Accessibility</h2>

        <p>Business analysts are involved in the design or modification of business systems or IT systems. They interact with business stakeholders and subject matter experts in order to understand their problems and needs. They gather, document and analyze business needs and requirements to help steer the team towards an end result that meets the organization's needs and expectations.</p>

        <h3>Key Responsibilities</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Ensuring accessibility requirements are included in business requirements documents</li>
            <li>Gathering accessibility needs from stakeholders and end users</li>
            <li>Analyzing business processes to identify accessibility barriers</li>
            <li>Documenting accessibility requirements in user stories and specifications</li>
            <li>Working with teams to understand accessibility implications of business decisions</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Focus Areas</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Requirements gathering with accessibility considerations</li>
            <li>Stakeholder engagement including users with disabilities</li>
            <li>Business process analysis for inclusive design</li>
            <li>Cost-benefit analysis of accessibility implementations</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Common Job Titles</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Business Analyst</li>
            <li>Client Sponsor</li>
            <li>Requirements Analyst</li>
            <li>System Analyst</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Key Deliverables</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Business requirements documents with accessibility requirements</li>
            <li>User stories that include accessibility acceptance criteria</li>
            <li>Process maps showing accessible workflows</li>
            <li>Stakeholder analysis including accessibility needs</li>
        </ul>
